properties.review_text_published:
Update 3/2024: I believe in giving second chances. I think this establishment has a different team in the kitchen. I ordered some of my favorites along with some new dishes and was not impressed.

Stuffed Tofu - total failure the filling tasted sour and not in savory way. Picture shows four but only received three.

Fried Rice w/Pickled Mustard Greens - Partial failure due to the lack of flavor. And the mustard green was not pickled at all.

Braised Tofu with Lemongrass Stalk - Good. Not like it was before. This was my favorite. Quality has gone down.

This is officially my last time eating here. I am super sad about this decision. üò•

Update 1/2024: I have been back to this restaurant twice this month and each time was not able to host my friends there. I bragged so much about the food and atmosphere and was completely disappointed once we got there to not be able to eat due to an issue in the kitchen and then a private event. Both can be accepted but disappointed nonetheless.

But my issue is with the staff. I am not sure what happened from last year to now but the staff is clearly not interested in working there. The front of the house staff seems to be in another world and definitely don't have a food service attitude. I can't imagine what is happening in the back of the house.

I cannot in good conscience keep championing this restaurant. They get two stars from me. I am seriously disappointed after having joyfully eaten here in the past.

2023 Review
I am declaring that this is the best plant-based restaurant in Da Nang. The food was absolutely delicious and was pleasantly plated. The proportion of the dishes matched the price point too.

I've been to many restaurants here in Da Nang and generally liked them all but Nha Hang Chay Tam Chau creates an atmospheric experience that enhances the food flow. The mantras set the mood. The lighting is super colorful and the table area are uniquely designed.

Overall, an upscale experience that I highly recommend.

The Banh Xeo was perfectly crisp and not oily with the right portion of fillings. A must have food sharing adventure.

The Lotus Nut Rice. Wow! A great combo to have with the Lemongrass Tofu. What a feast!

Thanks to the hard working chefs and the staff. I will definitely be back here for more. One thing to note, it's cash only. They don't accept credit cards.

I am a traveling plant-based chef specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

I came here for one thing and one thing only. The highly recommended Khao Soi. Wow! Now this is Khao Soi!

First of all, the creamy consistency from the.coconit milk is the way it's supposed to be done. Not oily and not watery at all!

Second, the spices were perfect, everything was balanced and create a nice harmony of flavors and textures.

This is indeed the best Vegan Khao Soi I have ever eaten. Definitely, the best in Chiang Rai.

The only thing I would add is textured mushrooms and kaffir lime leaf to give it that pungent umami flavor.

Very impressive. I am super picky when it comes Vegan Khao Soi. Not everyone makes it rich. This is why I am giving this a raving review.

properties.review_text_published:
One of the joyful things I enjoy about writing reviews is meeting the business owners and learning about their products/services. The team at Rahat Bakery is quite exceptional and it's reflected in their wonderful bread. Yumtastic!

Super fresh, great texture, and excellent flavor. There is nothing like a really great-tasting bread. Just five wholesome ingredients: flour, yeast, water, salt and sesame seeds.

I ate my first round delight with Mi Tron (Jackfruit Salad). What a nice combo. The bread is great for salads, soups, dips, and I already know some hummus and the bread would be amazing.

All I can say is this. Your bread is perfect! Keep making more.

If you are in Da Nang, do yourself a favor get over to Rahat Bakery and enjoy. (I am eating my last round now as I write this review.) As chef, I am thinking this bread would make great small pizzas. Add your sauce at home and your toppings pop into a toaster oven. Hint. Hint. Lol.

See you guys soon!

location.name: Water Drop Tea House Restaurant

properties.review_text_published:
When you first arrived it may not be very obvious there is a restaurant located here.

It's actually inside the Buddhist Temple.

The space is very beautiful, serene, and open. I did have to ask the attendant where is the restaurant because I still didn't noticed it right away. It is located your left.

Once inside you will sense the peaceful order of the space.

Now the food. The menu is simple and easy to flow with. Your order at the counter, pay and your dishes will be served at your table. The system is efficient and the food is prepared promptly.

I order the fried wonton, sauteed vegetables and fried noodles. Wontons are an absolute must order. The crispy texture and flavor were very good. I wish there was some spicy mustard for those.

The sauteed cabbage dish was good but only one thing, the cabbage is steamed without seasoning. However, you can do as I did mix the toppings with some soy sauce along with the cabbage. After that I tasted complete. I think ginger would have been a nice addition.

The fried noodles weren't exactly as I thought. I should have asked if they used rice noodles or wheat noodles for the preparation. I was expecting rice noodle since the dish was explain it was like pancit. With that to the side, it's was tasty and fresh. I did add soy sauce to boost the flavor.

The staff were very pleasant. The complete experience was indeed a pleasure. I hope they bring back the calamansi drink.

I will go next door to Mabuhay Tea House for more food exploration.

properties.review_text_published:
Beautiful restaurant and wonderful staff. I came here for dinner for the first time to explore several dishes.

The Bun Hue Soup is good for people who may be sensitive to the robust flavor of traditional Bun Hue. For me it was lacking and was more watered down. I've eaten vegan Bun Hue so many times that I can't count the bowls. I give it a 3 in flavor and 6 for presentation.

I also ordered the Bum Mam Chay - Seafood Noodle Salad. This dish has a really great sauce with a nice portion size for one person. Super fresh ingredients. 7 in flavor and same for presentation.

The prices are really good. The two dishes and a pineapple juice cost 75,000 VND.

I will come again to try the Cao Lau. Another traveler I met in Chiang Mai, Thailand stated it tastes better than what he experienced in Hoi An. Sounds like a worthy challenge. üôÇ I have a great reference for amazing Vegan Cao Lau from Hoi An. Let's go!

Update: Went the next day for the Cao Lau. Alright, as a chef and person the studies flavor profiles, this dish was monotone. Cao Lau should cover the spectrum sour, pungent, bitter, astringent and sweet. The broth was basic soy sauce. These best plant based Cao Lau I ate was indeed in Hoi An.

This one is good but missing the full range. Vegetables were very fresh. Excellent presentation. Noodles had a nice texture. I don't think they are made fresh or as fresh as in Hoi An.

I loved my stay here at WS Hostel. Very wonderful staff and team. Let's start by saying the photos match the actual property. Nothing overstated or oversold.

I appreciate honest listing. I stayed in 2.4 Queen Size Dorms which has only 4 beds on the floor. Great setup!

This has to be one of the top hostel experiences in Chiang Mai. Very modern facility with a  spacious setup. Smart layout throughout. Each section feels like your own space without feeling so cramped or stacked on top of each other.

Ample storage area, perfect location of power outlets and super comfy bed. I sleep well on firm beds. Each area comes with a locker, and several places to store your gear.

There are actually black out curtains. Unlike what other places promise.

This property would be 100% perfect if it weren't for the restaurant club a few meters away. They have live music and you can hear it at night from about 22:30 - 00:30.

Will I stay here again? Absolutely!!!

Keep in mind this place is popular so book in advance when possible.

Herbal Steam Sauna
This place is not a spa and doesn't pretend to be one either. Very basic and old. At first sight, you'll question why you are there. You definitely won't lounge around for long. Go for steam and keep it moving. Functional without the aesthetics.

Water, towel, sarong, tea, and scrub are provided for 200THB during your one hour timeframe.

Thai Massage
I had one massage here that was average at best, which is typical around town. I've been a resident at one point and massage student of a few teachers in Chiang Mai.

I will say getting a massage after the herbal steam sauna is good though.

Staff
Great personalities and pleasant to communicate with. Some do speak and understand English. If you know some Thai you'll have more engaging conversations.

location.name: B2 Chiang Rai Phahonyothin Hotel / ‡∏ö‡∏µ‡∏ó‡∏π ‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡∏£‡∏≤‡∏¢ ‡∏û‡∏´‡∏•‡πÇ‡∏¢‡∏ò‡∏¥‡∏ô

properties.review_text_published:
The staff are super awesome and friendly. I was happy with my interactions with them.

I stayed in Room 210 which seemed to be good and cozy. I'll share more on that in just a moment.

I loved the linens, towels, and firmness of the mattress. I wasn't hanging out in the room a lot to notice all the fine details. I did sleep well though and that is a plus.

On my day of check out, I noticed some of the other rooms. I had other rooms to compare Room 210 with.

The building is aging. Various things can be easily seen before you enter the premises.

One is the huge hole in the architectural structure in the front of the building. One of the panels is damaged.

Back to the room. Room 210 flooring needs attention. There are chips in the tile floor. And the tile nearest the door moves when you walk on it. The bathroom tiles around the shower are bulging out due to water damage. The headboard looks beaten with damage with paint covering it.

I happened to see the other neighboring rooms because the doors were open for housekeeping. And they looked better than the one I was in.

I would stay here again but not in Room 210. I noticed that 209 has a completely different flooring type and the interior style looks more inviting.

Keep in mind there is no soundproofing! I was lucky there weren't any noisy neighbors during the night. I could hear the person on the next room rearranging their luggage. You can hear everything.

Thanks again to the wonderful staff.

The beds are super firm just the way I like them. Clean linens and great towels. They supply towels, bottled water, soap, and shampoo.

I stayed for nearly two weeks and was happy with my time there.

The only issue I had was with the bathroom function of the shower. The position is quite wrong for a wet bath of this type. You'll have to tread through water upon entering the bathroom. The water doesn't drain downwards to the drain.

I would consider staying here in the future. A good option for the price.

When traveling I always seek out family owned businesses. I love the level of care that is given by the host. I appreciate the connections blended with the home feeling. I got all that and more.

Ty House is wonderfully located in a Vietnamese neighborhood with access to lots of great amenities and restaurants.

I love that I could walk daily to the local market for fresh fruits and vegetables, vegan Banh Mi and vegan food.

The apartment is a well designed with ample storage for all your things. Even the fridge can accommodate a week's worth of food.

And to top every else the wifi is super fast. See screenshot.

The host lives on site so you don't have to deal with an absent host. She communicates frequently and is available to assist with recommendations.

I originally booked for two weeks. I was so impressed that I added another week. I will definitely stay here again when I am back in Danang.

Update back again for another two weeks. Feels like home here. The family gave me a warm welcome.

location.name: V.Napaphud Vegetarian Food

properties.review_text_published:
This restaurant really surprised me tonight. I didn't have much expectation because of the ambiance. The seating felt like it was just plopped into a neighborhood veg store. To be clear it's not a romantic setting.

I ordered Pad See Ew. Wow! It tasted amazing. It had the right combination of sweet and savory. But not overdone either.

The noodles could have been seared a little longer but that didn't stop the goodness from flowing. I enjoyed it completely.

I plan on coming more often to explore the menu. The prices are really good and the portions are satisfying.

I am a traveling plant-based chef specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: 1/8 - 1/9 Chaiyapoom Soi1, Si phum, Chang Moi, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: Baan Heart Thai

questions.question: Noteworthy details
questions.text_answer: The mornings here are super peaceful. I found myself easing into my day with a great flow.

questions.question: Can you share more about these topics?

properties.review_text_published:
Impressive hostel. Two Star Hostel with Five Star Service.

It's been a moment since I last stayed at a hostel and this property is quite good. Very clean space and the towel and bed linens were fabulous.

I am definitely planning on staying again in the future. Love the firmness of the bed. Rested super well. The street can get loud at night towards the weekends due to super rowdy travelers at the nearby spots on the same street. Ear plugs might be needed.

The actual guests were super conscious to not make noise in the night. I stayed on the fourth floor that has the queen size beds. Loved the design and comfort.

Lot of ample key card security points to assure everyone safety and camera strategically placed as well to monitor the public spaces. Community sitting area inside and in the garden. Space to store food in the fridge as well.

Overall, very accommodating and friendly space with good vibes.

Khap Khun Khrap to the Baan Heart Thai team.

location.address: 75, 5 Muang Samut Rd, Tambon Chang Moi, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50300, Thailand
location.name: Kanchan Indian Food (Home Made, Pure Veg)

properties.review_text_published:
I felt deflated after reading all the wonderful reviews here on Google Maps.

I ordered what's basically considered staples in the Indian cuisine Gobi Aloo and Dal.

First the Dal was very basic. It was lacking the variety of spices that I know that goes into Dal.

The second, the Gobi Aloo wasn't prepared like a typical Gobi Aloo. It was prepared like a Manchurian Gobi with tomato sauce. I wouldn't have minded if the flavor profile was there.

In short, what I received didn't match what I've read here. Nice family and love the concept of home style cooking in a home. It has potential. üôèüèæ

properties.review_text_published:
My first Vipassana course took place here. The staff were very very helpful during the reception intake process. They all were very joyful and eager to assist.

The course was absolutely a life long gift for myself. The process, the teachings and the wisdom afforded me a journey within the transformation of my mind unlike anything I have experienced before.

Vipassana is a very powerful practice that will lead those that sincerely participate to a liberated life and mind of true happiness.

I personally had a profound experience that taught me the depth of how much we carry from not only this life but the experiences we can carry from previous generations.

I cannot say enough of how much I gained. I highly recommend anyone that is on the path of seeking the truth as it is without interpretation or persuasion, you can discover how Vipassana can work for you. By our own efforts can we be liberated from suffering.

I love love the firmness of the king sized bed. I get the best sleep here. The location is perfect. Central enough to get to the main shopping stores within minutes. Great area to walk for street food. Which is available at various points throughout the day.

You can hear birds chirping in the early AM. And at night the street is quiet. I definitely recommend staying here during your visit to Chiang Mai.

Today, I ate very well. First, the owner (Tio) of the establishment is kind and dedicated to food service.

I watched her prepare several meals for customers with the same level of intention for each bowl served.

Although, it's outside the main city area, I was lucky to pick a hotel that is in walking distance. It's a typical local Thai restaurant layout but clean. In other words nothing fancy. But don't let that stop you from coming.

Now about the food. I am super pleased with the fresh pan seared wontons I ordered today. Nice range of flavors that was complimented with healthy portion sizes. Let's talk about the noodles. Wow! Very good quality and made the experience even more enjoyable. Completely satisfied.

The noodles are made inhouse and they are suitable for vegetarians. They do contain egg. The wontons are vegan.

This little shop is delivering big flavors. I'll be back for sure.

properties.review_text_published:
Excellent location in Santiham. The room was convenient and quiet. I slept very well at Pha Fan Hotel. Great linen and towels. Spacious modern room and I was happy it had a desk and fridge.

The only draw back for me is they don't have an online booking system. You have to book via the chat feature of Google Maps.

I wanted to stay for one week but not possible this time. I would stay again in the future. Stayed two nights. Not sure what the system is for housekeeping. It wasn't mentioned and wasn't provided.

Perhaps most guests stay a night or two.

They only accept cash. Wifi was fast and consistent. That is another plus.

Overall, the location was great for me. I would stay here again.

properties.review_text_published:
I've been a patron since 2013. I usually purchase fruit smoothies and fresh juice blends.

The prices have changes since then. Small smoothie is 45THB and large 60THB.

The best juices and smoothies in Chiang Mai. Why? No ice. No water. No sugar. The  smoothies are perfectly blended to a creamy consistency. The fruit is always ripe and naturally sweet.

No matter how much time passes over the years I can trust The Juice House to deliver every time. I get my daily dose of goodness twice a day.

I am equally grateful for their consistency and quality.

I am a traveling plant-based chef specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

properties.review_text_published:
First upon arrival the staff is very friendly. The check in process is smooth. You can tell they have been well trained on making sure guest are welcomed. I came very early before checkin but they provided a secure room for my bags.

The hostel is plush. I have never seen such a clean and well designed space like this. The attention to details is very impressed. This is five star hostel experience.

The bed linen‚Ä¶ Wow. My first thought was "This is better that some of the hotels in Chiang Mai." The bathrooms are very clean. There are locker with ample space for you gear. Each bed unit has it's own light and power supply with a nifty ledge to place your computer or devices. Two clean toilets, sink and showers. The room has air conditioning as well.

They provided vegetarian food for the guests. And complimentary tea, coffee, water and toast for breakfast. And tea, coffee and water anytime. A1 service from every staff member.

And I sleep extremely well. This is sometime rare for me in other hostels. Seems like the Green Tiger attracts good people. And the WIFI is blazing fast.

I highly recommend this hotel/restaurant when you visit Chiang Mai. You will not be disappointed.

Historical monument acknowledging the Three Kings that founded the ancient city of Chiang Mai also know as the Rose of the North.

You will see realistic sculptures of Kings Mengrai, Ramkamhaeng and Ngam Muang.

The area directly around the monument is treated sacred. Please treat the area with respect.

properties.review_text_published:
Very popular location for photos and video. It's the East Main gate of the Old City of Chiang Mai.

The blend of the ancient and modern can be experienced within the walls of the old city. Much of the perseveration of antiquity can still be witnessed by visiting the Temples (Wats) within the moated section of the city.

Definitely, recommend visiting and filling your memories with iconic photos to share with family and friends.

properties.review_text_published:
Modern and cozy shop is conveniently located in the Wulai area of the city.

This tiny shop is delivering big flavors with crafted kombuchas. They certainly put the aaaahhh in kombucha.

I was introduced to the goodness by my Thai friend and I was hooked after that.

I came to explore the other flavors in person. I got one liter of the passion fruit and mango. Soooooo good. Arroy mak mak.

Excellent prices and great quality. I've tasted quite a bit of buchas and this is some of the best I've ever had.

properties.review_text_published:
Tien Sieng is a long standing contributer to vegan and vegetarian food in Chiang Mai. The mission is one of compassion and gratitude.

The staff are dedicated to their customers in hope we all gravitate towards a life that does no harm.

And now onto the food. The food is very tasty and freshly made each opening day. They will not serve day old food.

The prices are great so they can serve everyone the community. I highly recommend Tien Sieng.

They also sell vegetarian and vegan products as well. Those that live in Chiang Mai can get all sorts of plant-based products from Taiwan.

Find you way to Tien Sieng for a peaceful karma free plate.

The team at WebbCam are super awesome and knowledgable. You will definitely leave their shop with confidence that you have purchase the right gear.

They are professional and enthusiastic about photography. I highly recommend going there to explore great gear at the right prices.

And I am not sure what part of it was supposed to be a salad. Seems like they didn't have all the ingredients to make the dish. Certainly didn't look like anything people posted in their review pictures of the yellow noodle salad.

Won't be supporting the restaurant at all. Sorry guys but I think you need to reevaluate this menu item.

Suksama!

properties.review_text_published:
Small shop but big on flavors. They are dedicated to delivering honest good food.

The flavor profiles are authentic. I felt like I ate at a family home. The Vegan Nasi Campur is the best I've had in Ubud. Absolutely, the best. Highly recommend it.

Everything was uniquely flavor so it made every bite a full delight.

I didn't stop at one dish. I ordered the Tempe and tofu with sauce. That sauced is the truth! Homemade and wholesome.

The rooms I was shown were old and musty. Smelled like mildew. I am sensitive to mold. Cancelled my booking.

I can't recommend this property. The listing photos look great but the actual rooms were very disappointing. This is my first trip to Bali I became instantly deflated after this being it was my first day to Ubud.

The managing staff person was super friendly and understanding. He was in agreement in assisting me with cancelling the booking.

I hope the owner/management addresses the conditions mentioned. Considering Ubud is a place of wellness, having mildew and musty conditions are so contradictory.

Very lovely restaurant that offers very fresh vegan food. The quality is very good. The flavors are delightful. I would prefer the flavors to be in more depth. But it's a buffet and has to accommodate as many dietary preferences.

With that I enjoyed all the dishes I ate. Very wholesome and delightful.

The price is super good (50k IDR). There is a fresh salad bar with a nice selection of dressings. There is a soup which I found to be very tasty. And the hot bar items had enough items to accommodate everyone. The ratio of Balinese dishes to general one are balanced.

The Indonesian dishes were tasty. I can tell that the flavor profiles are geared towards Westerners. But don't let that deter you. I am speaking from a chef's point of view.

Go enjoyed and be nourished.

I wouldn't say this is the best representation of Balinese food. Price is good in comparison to local prices.

But for 50k I could have eaten at another establishment with everything made fresh and much brighter environment. Hope this helps the next traveler.

A must experience of cultural exploration and historical flow into the blend of ancient culture of Hinduism influence in Vietnam. And for those that understand the roots of Hinduism, you will see a clear examples rooted in SanƒÅtana Dharma.

There are many examples that reflect on the balance between the feminine and masculine energy in form and fashion. These visual reminders were created as a way for practitioners to focus on the devoted path to honor nature and the eternal way of the truth and light.

location.address: 56 Ho√†ng B√≠ch S∆°n, An H·∫£i B·∫Øc, S∆°n Tr√†, ƒê√† N·∫µng 550000, Vietnam

properties.review_text_published:
Update: Came again to give them a second chance. Twice disappointed. Even after sending a message on Zalo. I was told there are dishes without onion and garlic. Got there and the only two things is fresh spring roll and salad. Good thing Tam Chau is just down the street. Not a total wasted of time. Definitely, not coming back here.

Nice looking macrobiotic restaurant. I hope that the hours are correct now.

Went there to enjoy a large dinner with a friend but the menu was rendered to four items because they closing at 15:30 PM and not 20:30 PM as listed on the Google Map page. Perhaps they don't manage the Google Maps Business page. That is understandable. I hope it is corrected.

The waitstaff seemed to be distracted and more focused with her phone. And somewhere between placing the order and her giving it to the kitchen she didn't tell them no onions. Which I said a few times and she appeared to have acknowledge that I said no onions. The bowl came with onions and quickly taken away to have the onions picked off the top of the salad.

Having been in food service it is important to communicate to the kitchen when a customer make a request for something not to be on the dish to make certain the kitchen is aware. I recommend you having customers write down their orders. It will eliminate missing requests.

It was apparently closing time so there were no pleasantries exchanged during the 30 minutes of being there. There was one woman there appeared to be an owner. She appeared not to be in  pleasant mood. Not sure what that was about. I won't be going back.

Veganism is more than just food. It should express a spirit of compassion and joy. As vegans we are here to reduced the suffering in the world. If we aren't able to do that with our interactions then what is the point.

properties.review_text_published:
Very nice ambiance and super wonderful staff. Our server was pleasant and joyful with reviewing the menu with us. Thank you J you were the best.

The pure juices were very good. We ordered the Pure Gold blend. Not sure if they produce the juices inhouse or not. I forgot to ask.

I ordered the Pad Thai. It was not the way Pad Thai should be made. I am sharing these points with hope the management reads this as constructive feedback from one culinary artist to another. I have 20 years of vegan and vegetarian culinary experience.

The way this dish was prepared was more like a pasta dish with sauce and not like traditional Pad Thai.

First, the sauce is overbearing sour due to there being too much tamarind paste. There need to be a light flavor of tamarind with and even blend of palm sugar. If not palm sugar then you can use coconut sugar. I know this is typically made with fish sauce. There is a really great alternative for fish sauce made from fermented pineapples. There is vegan "fish sauce" from Vietnam that is the best Nuoc Nam Chay.

Second, Pad Thai is one of the most simplest Thai dishes to prepare. I lived in Thai for five years and have taken numerous classes to learn the cuisine. I recommend someone from your team take time to learn the proper way this dish is made. Especially, the way to prepare the noodles.

Lastly, presentation. What was shown on the menu and what was served were two different presentations. Not very inviting. Everything was mixed together and didn't look like it was handled with care.

The staff has a lot of enthusiasm which makes this establishment a winner for personality. I think with some good direction and mastery, the meals will rank very high in the future.

location.name: Polar Boulangerie and Patisserie

properties.review_text_published:
Very nice garden ambiance and friendly staff. Nice quiet environment for meetings or simple getaway in a green space. There is indoor and outdoor seating with convenient spacing for privacy.

I enjoyed a tasty tropical fruit smoothie. The staff were kind to allow me to eat my lunch there and supply me with a plate. I am super grateful for their thoughtfulness and attention.

I am a traveling vegan chef specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: No. 53Ëôü, Zhongyuan St, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491
location.name: Jiyuan APT

properties.review_text_published:
I chose this property for it's convenience of it's location to close proximity to several vegetarian restaurants and the price.

There was a slight mixup with the room but that was fixed immediately. Super grateful for the responsiveness.

Be mindful this is a self check in hotel. The process has several steps so it's best to exercise patience during your arrival. I think several reviews already noted the steps.

Note to foreign travelers: Make sure you download the Line app prior to arrival. You will need that as part of the check in process.

The building is small and so are the rooms. However, they are modern with basic amenities: bottled water, shower gel soap, toothbrushes, electric kettle (no tea or coffee - bring your own) plus tea cups and a fridge.

The hot water shower is awesome. I would consider staying here again in the future.

I am a traveling vegan chef specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: 14 Phra Pok Klao Rd Soi 4, Tambon Phra Sing, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: Kalm‚Äã Village‚Äã Chiangmai

properties.review_text_published:
This impressive architectural design is conveniently located near Chiang Mai gate in the Old City.

And what an amazing transformation to this area of the city. The levels of creativity and attention to details with amazing views throughout the building are incredible.

I came here with a few friends and we were in awe of the exhibits, facilities, and the shops.

Kalm Village is a golden gem that is preserving the Thai traditions of art and culture with a modem flair. Loved every minute of my time during my visit.

Highly recommended!

I am a traveling vegan chef that specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: No. 26‰πã1Ëôü, Lane 199, Jilin Rd, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491
location.name: Ê≤õÁÄÖÁ¥†È£üÈ§®

properties.review_text_published:
I ordered the braised wontons with chili sauce. I thought the price was a bit pricey $80 compared to other nearby locations around the city. And the way the place looks. The atmosphere is grungy and old.

Now about the meal. The wontons were made just right. Very good texture and the fillings was surprisingly delicious. Just enough chili oil to spark the taste buds even more.

I have to admit, I did set my expectations a little low because of the way the place looked. I was indeed surprised with every bite.

The menu is completely in Chinese. You might need to rely on Google Translate and photos from shared by other customers.

I am a traveling vegan chef that specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: No. 23Ëôü, Lane 97, Songjiang Rd, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491
location.name: Paramita

properties.review_text_published:
Highly recommend this small shop of deliciousness. I went around 11 AM and they staff were super busy preparing orders. I was happy to see the flow of so many orders. Definitely, boosted my confidence that I would submerge myself into a world  of yum.

The ambiance is basic and nothing fancy. It is about the food. I enjoyed two plates of the selections they offered. I imagine each day there is a fresh variety to choose from.

What I enjoyed the most was the distinction of flavors in each dish. Super tasty.

I am a traveling vegan chef that specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: No. 1Ëôü, Section 1, Chengde Rd, Datong District, Taipei City, Taiwan 103
location.name: Minder Vegetarian QSquare Taipei Branch

properties.review_text_published:
Highly recommended! Huge selection of freshly prepared vegetarian/ vegan delights. I sampled as much as I could to get a sense of their offerings.

Everything was super delightful and tasty. There were some dishes that I could have easily enjoyed more. Very clean and organized. I have to check out their other locations.

I highly recommend the curry pockets. Wow! I wish I had more room to eat more. I was pleasantly stuffed. And there is a small selection of sweet treats. I had the mochi with bean paste. Incredible flavor. And a nice finish to the meal.

I wish they sold some type of beverage, like an herbal tea.

The system is efficient. Grab a plate and tongs. Choose from the wide variety of goodness. Weight the plate and pay. A find somewhere to sit and eat. You can also do a takeaway box for those on the go.

Lastly, the price is absolutely great! I could eat here everyday just explore all the options. The dishes are onion and garlic free.

I am a traveling vegan chef that specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: No. 61Ëôü, Lane 330, Songjiang Rd, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491
location.name: Ë∂äÂçóÈ§äË∫´Á¥†È£ü

properties.review_text_published:
July 11th, 2023 - Came here to enjoy the food but unfortunately the shop is closed due to no staff. Chatted with the owner.

She said she will post when they are open again.

location.address: No. 1Ëôü, Section 1, Chengde Rd, Datong District, Taipei City, Taiwan 103
location.name: Q Square Mall

location.address: WR3P+M7R, Prasopsook Rd, Tambon Wiang, Mueang Chiang Rai District, Chiang Rai 57000, Thailand
location.name: Imboonbarame (Vegetarian / Vegan)

properties.review_text_published:
The owner needs to seriously add macrobiotic food in the name of the business.

What I ate to today was shockingly bland. It was so tasteless that I couldn't finish the plate. It was like something you serve someone in a hospital on a low sodium and diabetic diet. If that suits you then this is the place for you.

All three of the sides were tasteless. Something to the equivalent of textured water. I could understand one dish being this way, but all of the dishes and the rice. I had to ask what is going on with the food.

According to the owner and based on her explanation this is definitely macrobiotic food establishment.

Sorry, but there is no way this is the best Jai food in Thailand as previous comments stated. I will never eat here again. Up to you if you do.

I am a traveling vegan chef that specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: 61, 86 ‡∏ñ‡∏ô‡∏ô Rajdejdamrong Rd, Wiang, Mueang Chiang Rai District, Chiang Rai 57000, Thailand
location.name: Local Thai Vegan restaurant

properties.review_text_published:
This location reminds of the shack like family restaurants you find on the roadside around the world whereas the cooks are underated because the aesthetic of the business.

I had two dishes and both were tasty. The flavor profiles were on the safe side though. But definitely, better than the two other locations I reviewed in Chiang Rai. And all dishes are made fresh to order.

Food aside the owners are very kind and dedicated to serving the community with karma free meals.

I do wish the place was cleaner and more tidy.

All the dishes are vegan and are suitable for those that eat Jain, Sattvic or Daoist diets which are allium free. No onion, garlic, leeks, chives, scallions.

I am a traveling vegan chef that specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: WR6H+98G, Tambon Wiang, Mueang Chiang Rai District, Chiang Rai 57000, Thailand
location.name: Yota Vegetarian Foods

properties.review_text_published:
This business listing is the same as Local Thai Vegan restaurant. Not sure why there are two listings. Perhaps a customer created without knowing.

This is indeed a local Thai restaurant. Not the type of place for a date. More like eat and go.

The owners are very kind and joyful. They are Jai practitioners that are helping spread the good way in Chiang Rai.

All the signs are in Thai so might fill a bit overwhelmed trying to sort things out. But don't worry they have a English menu.

I order Noodle Salad and Pad See Ew. Simple flavors made with kindness.

location.address: 414 Sanambin Rd, Tambon Wiang, Mueang Chiang Rai District, Chiang Rai 57000, Thailand
location.name: Tamachat Vegetarian Restaurant.

properties.review_text_published:
Came for the Khao Soi as recommended in the reviews. I am sorry but the Khao Soi I was served was not that good not authentic. I've had much much better in Chiang Mai.

The dish was oily, definitely different style of noodles, and an overall lack depth of curry flavor and spices. I dared not drink the broth to spare my stomach from any probable episodes. I doubt I will return here.

I am a traveling vegan chef that specializing in food science and flavorology. Check out my other reviews on Google Maps.

location.address: WR4P+52P, Tambon Wiang, Mueang Chiang Rai District, Chiang Rai 57000, Thailand
location.name: Oasis Vegetarian

properties.review_text_published:
I have to admit I am spoiled by the spice masters in Chiang Mai. The atmosphere is very quiet and peaceful.

However, the food reflect the same sentiment. There was a lack of flavor. No variations of flavor. The fried veg rice was boring and dry.

I left there not feeling satisfied and disappointed. What a shame! Vegan / Vegetarian food can be so adventurous for the tastebuds with just a few ingredients and spice combinations.

location.address: 25 Suthep Road , Srivichai Soi Suthep, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: 100 Flavors: Chiang Mai Craft Ice Cream

properties.review_text_published:
100 Flavors is a dessert exploration that you cannot miss while you are in Chiang Mai. Over one hundred flavors are handcrafted to export you to ice cream nirvana. Come with a group or come alone it doesn't matter.

100 Flavors continues to deliver excellence every time. I've been coming here since 2013. The majority of the flavors are vegan made from coconut cream.

You are in for a treat!

location.address: 42 Mahidol Rd, Tambon Su Thep, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: ‡∏ä‡∏°‡∏£‡∏°‡∏°‡∏±‡∏á‡∏™‡∏ß‡∏¥‡∏£‡∏±‡∏ï‡∏¥ ‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏°‡πà Chiang Mai Vegetarian society

properties.review_text_published:
I always enjoy coming to the restaurant and the store. Keep in mind you have to take the food away. COVID had changed the flow of many operations in Thailand.

I remembered when you could get soups and other food prepared on the spot. And a bigger selection of dishes.

Around 9:45 AM the food trays were just about empty. I am not sure how often they replenish the trays.

However, I filled up on the juices and teas. Most have English on the labels. There were a few that were labeled in Thai only. I used Google Translate to sort it out.

I highly recommend going to the goods shop for teas, snacks, grains, oil, body care products, etc. all priced amazingly low.

Part of their mission is recycling and reuse. You will find a huge selection of second hand clothing and other donated items at super low prices.

Lastly, they have fresh organic produce available too. Go explore and enjoy.

location.address: RX2J+239, Tambon Chang Phueak, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: Sangwiroon Vegetarian

properties.review_text_published:
My all time favorite restaurant in Santitham. This family is dedicated to serving the vegan community with blessed foods of the best quality. Everything is made fresh each day.

No leftovers from the day before are served. Which is very difficult because they sell out daily.

I highly recommend exploring all the dishes served. My top favorite is the Khao Soi. Fresh ingredients bathed in a coconut milk based with pickled cabbage and vegan mushroom based product that will dazzle the tastebuds of most omnivores. The fried noodles are very tasty and the soup has a very nice depth of flavors.

This is one of a few actual Jai restaurants in Chiang Mai that are are practitioners of  the Dao faith. They are vegan themselves and also follow the strict parameters of a satvic diet. No onion, garlic, leeks, chives, and scallions.

You can trust that they will deliver the flavors at the best price point in Chiang Mai.

location.address: ‡∏´‡∏°‡∏π‡πà‡∏ó‡∏µ‡πà 1 149 Mae Hi, Pai District, Mae Hong Son 58130, Thailand
location.name: Canary Guesthouse

properties.review_text_published:
Absolutely loved my stay at Canary Guesthouse. The room was perfect, quiet, and clean.

Impressive interior design and I was most pleased with how cozy the room felt. I slept very very well. This was my first stay here but not my last time for sure.

The staff were very kind and  communicated in English. I greatly appreciated their hospitality and service.

I look forward to stay here again. A huge thank you to the Canary Guesthouse Team.

location.address: 9C4Q+RQ9, Pai, Pai District, Mae Hong Son 58130, Thailand
location.name: Ci Xin Jai

properties.review_text_published:
Great taste and excellent price for fresh vegan food in Pai. Ci Xin Jai is the truth!

All the dishes offered are made fresh daily. The staff are dedicated to serving pure vegan food for Thais and travelers a like.

Come ready to eat because you are in for a treat. The clear noodle soup is great to start you meal afterwards you can choose the various dishes in the case. Typical Thai style. Or you can order from the menu. They make fried spring rolls and fried mock chicken as well.

I've been a customer since 2013 and have been treated with kindness every time I have stayed in Pai.

If you have time explore the menu. There is a wide range of dishes for everyone. I do recommend the Som Tum (Green Papaya Salad) and Pad See Ew (Pan Fried Wide Noodles).

All the dishes serves here are free of alliums (onion, garlic, leeks, chives, and scallions). But don't worry the dishes are super delicious.

location.address: 9C5R+9M2, Pai, Pai District, Mae Hong Son 58130, Thailand
location.name: On Massage

properties.review_text_published:
On Massage is healing gem in Pai. Khun On is a master Thai massage practitioner.

I make sure to get multiple massage treatments with her everytime I am in Pai.

She is super skilled and dedicated to providing uplifting Thai massage sessions. She is authentic and kind. And the prices are excellent!

I've been a customer since 2013.

location.address: 98 Rachadamnoen Rd Soi 4, Si Phum Sub-district, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: Ming Kwan Vegetarian Restaurant

properties.review_text_published:
I've been a frequent customer of Ming Kwan for 7 years. I am always satisfied with their offerings and prices. The ladies there work very hard to feed the local community and travelers as well.

They are dedicated to the real and true Jai cooking. No onion, garlic, leeks, chives, scallions, etc. And without sacrificing the rich flavors of northern Thailand.

The dishes are well balanced in taste and nutrition.

I highly recommend their Khao Soi curry noodle soup. It is super rich taste that has a depth of care that will satisfy your tastebuds. And the portion is healthy. So come ready to feast.

You have to also try their meaty mushroom. Chewy savory goodness. I think they prepare the best mushrooms in Chiang Mai. There is also some of the most amazing vegan sausages that are spicy and savory.

They are part of my top five must eat at restaurants in Chiang Mai.

Enjoy!

location.address: Haiya Sub-district, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50100, Thailand
location.name: Thong Nam Nueng Thai Massage

properties.review_text_published:
There are hundreds of massage businesses in Chiang Mai. And it's is hard to determine which provides the best and consistent treatments.

I've been extremely fortunate to have been introduced to this family when I first arrived in Chiang Mai back in 2013.

My first treatment was from Kru Thong (mother of Nueng, the owner). Kru Thong is a master teacher and an exceptional practitioner. I was amazed during my first visit to the shop at how fast she was able to locate my issue and release the nerve blockage. I am still amazed how she was able to do what she did by only asking one question. I later became her student to learn about their system of treatment.

I am now close with the family and it's an honor to write this recommendation for this business.

Basically, don't miss their services whenever you are in Chiang Mai. They are one of few businesses that have maintain the authentic healing practice of Traditional Thai Therapeutic Massage treatment.

The facility is very clean and serene. The staff are all well trained and dedicated to their customers healing.

They also have a wide range of certified practitioners to manage different body types and conditions. Their healing balms are really good too. I also recommend that herbal ball treatment service. Helps relieve muscle tension and body stress.

I highly recommend scheduling a two hour treatment because one hour is not enough.

This business is a hidden gem in Chiang Mai. See for yourself and receive the goodness. I've introduced lots of people to Thong Nom Nueng.

location.address: 7QWX+3QW, Ban Hong, Ban Hong District, Lamphun 51130, Thailand
location.name: Wat Pa Khantitham

properties.review_text_published:
I received an invitation to spend three nights at this uplifting temple. I can say it was truly an honor to uphold the eight precepts in such a place of high integrity.

I learned so much during my time there. The transmissions I received were not only transformational, I am also deeply encouraged to share the Dharma so that others will find their way home.

I am grateful for Phra Ajaan Ly for opening the way and for Phra Ajaan Wit for his generosity in sharing the true way to end suffering.

Wat Pa Khantitham is a true lighthouse for those that are seeking for the truth.

location.address: 1, 4 Suriyawong Alley, Haiya Sub-district, Amphoe Mueang Chiang Mai, Chang Wat Chiang Mai 50100, Thailand
location.name: Aum Vegetarian Restaurant

properties.review_text_published:
I first experience the joy of Aum when they were located by Tha Phae gate. It's has always been a favorite for foodies from every corner of the world.

I highly recommend the Khao Soi and Som Tum (Papaya Salad) both are full flavor with the right presentation to leave you with a lifetime of memories.

The food is guaranteed to satisfy you. And the wonderful staff will make sure you eat well with their Northern Lanna hospitality.

Oh, I almost forgot to mention their amazing Massaman Curry. Yumtastic!

location.address: Wichayanon Rd, Tambon Chang Moi, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50300, Thailand
location.name: Warorot Market (Kad Luang)

properties.review_text_published:
Landmark market in Chiang Mai located near the Ping River.

This market is great for tourists to purchase an array of keepsakes, snacks, and clothing along with street food.

This bustling market is an adventure worth exploring and definitely a photographer's visual canvas to capture the raw expressions of Chiang Mai.

You'll find various areas to explore local northern style dishes and beverages. The prices are very good too.

I would plan to spend about one hour to explore Warorot Market. It is easy to get to by the red truck or you can even walk from Tha Phae gate. It's your preference.

I recommend trying out the local snacks and sweets. They might be different but they are really delicious. Arroy Dee!

location.address: 269/1 Changpuak Rd, Tambon Chang Phueak, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50300, Thailand
location.name: Vegetarian Food Ratsamitham Foundation

properties.review_text_published:
I think this is the best tasting vegetarian food of this type of all the local Thai restaurant in Chiang Mai.

There is a full depth of flavors in each dish. No bland food here at all.

Must try the Khao Soi. Very good flavor and presentation. See photo. Also, the vegan sausages are really tasty. Not a fan of the mushroom balls. They aren't very flavorful. But they don't make these.

You can also get rice with a selection of prepared dishes for a really great price. Excellent value overall.

They have a nice selection of snacks as well. The owners are calm and keep the atmosphere very peaceful.

location.address: Rachadamnoen Rd, Tambon Si Phum, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: Tha Phae Walking Street

properties.review_text_published:
An experience that you must not miss. There are handicrafts, textiles, gift items and lots of street food for everyone to enjoy. You can also get massages right on the walking street.

I recommend wearing comfortable walking shoes and plan to be there a few hours so you can explore everything.

Most travelers try to arrive just before 18:00 to witness the national anthem playing on the loud speakers and seeing everyone come to a stop to respect the anthem.

I enjoy going to support the local vendors and artisans.

location.address: 4/2 ‡∏ñ‡∏ô‡∏ô ‡∏´‡∏±‡∏™‡∏î‡∏¥‡πÄ‡∏™‡∏ß‡∏µ Si Phum Sub-district, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: glin.cafe

properties.review_text_published:
Modern minimalist interior design which makes for a really great spot for photos.

Simple menu with easy selections. The lychee and soda is a must try. Very nice presentation and super flavorful.

location.address: 50/5 ‡∏ñ‡∏ô‡∏ô ‡∏´‡∏±‡∏™‡∏î‡∏¥‡πÄ‡∏™‡∏ß‡∏µ Chang Phueak, ‡πÄ‡∏°‡∏∑‡∏≠‡∏á Chiang Mai 50300, Thailand
location.name: ‡∏Å‡∏¥‡∏ô‡∏ú‡∏±‡∏Å ‡∏Ñ‡∏≤‡πÄ‡∏ü‡πà Kinphak cafe (Cmu vegan Food) ‡∏≠‡∏≤‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏£‡πÄ‡∏à Vegan and Vegetarian Food

properties.review_text_published:
I am conflicted with my most current experience. I ordered the massaman curry with rice dish.

I usually get the papaya salad. Which is made to order and super delicious.

Clearly this massablah curry dish has already been prepared a few days ago. It's oily and tastes horrible. I ate one potato and I couldn't subject myself to eating any more. I am a chef and I know when potatoes have been sitting a few days and reheated.

It tastes like it looks (see photo). I say pull it off your menu since you don't make it fresh. It's not good.

I brought this to the attention of the owner in English and in Thai. And my observation is correct. It's not made fresh.

I can only recommend the one thing that I have ordered three times now and that is the papaya salad.

Good luck and enjoy.

Head up on the orange juice that says it's 100%. This is from an outside vendor. It definitely has sugar. It was super sweet beyond normal sweetness. I had to dilute with half water. Heads up to anyone that has a sugar free diet. I was told it had no sugar when I asked.

location.address: 51, Jalan Burma, 10050 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
location.name: Soy~UniQ

properties.review_text_published:
Top quality is the first words that come to mind. Highly recommend the dessert tofu with the ginger black sugar syrup. Super delicious. If you are in Penang make sure to add this shop to your list. And another must is the nutmeg fruit juice. The best I've had in Penang. Super refreshing and a nice addition to your dessert tofu.

My only regret was not stopping in sooner to explore the whole menu. Next time for sure.

location.address: RX4P+68P, Tambon Chang Phueak, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50300, Thailand
location.name: Bangkok Bank (BBL) - ‡∏ò‡∏ô‡∏≤‡∏Ñ‡∏≤‡∏£‡∏Å‡∏£‡∏∏‡∏á‡πÄ‡∏ó‡∏û‡∏Ø

properties.review_text_published:
The staff were very helpful in explaining the requirements to open an account.

Spoke English very well.

location.address: 68/6 Rachadamnoen Rd, Tambon Si Phum, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand
location.name: Chiangmai Foot Massage

properties.review_text_published:
I've have been a frequent customer here over the years. The previous practitioners were thorough and experts at delivery reflexology.

The foot massage I received today was a joke. Nothing short of a lazy foot rub. I watched a few other customers get the same lazy foot rub. I did not get what I paid for.

There was another practitioner that look like he knew what he was doing.

You lost my business. Sorry but I have to tell the truth.

location.address: Arked Penang 1, L1 , Komtar , Jalan Penang , Georgetown , 10000 Puala Pinang, 10300, Malaysia
location.name: Komtar Watch & Clock

properties.review_text_published:
Very friendly owner and nice selection of watches at this shop. I purchased a Casio watch for a reasonable price.

I would purchase from this shop again.

location.address: 96 1-2 ‡∏ñ‡∏ô‡∏ô ‡∏®‡∏£‡∏µ‡∏ô‡∏Ñ‡∏£‡∏¥‡∏ô‡∏ó‡∏£‡πå, Samrong Nuea, Mueang Samut Prakan District, Samut Prakan 10270, Thailand
location.name: ‡∏≠‡∏≤‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏£‡πÄ‡∏à ‡πÄ‡∏à‡πä‡∏ô‡πâ‡∏≠‡∏¢ ‡∏ï‡∏•‡∏≤‡∏î‡∏™‡∏≥‡πÇ‡∏£‡∏á

properties.review_text_published:
Pure vegetarian food made with love. The owner is a very kind Thai woman that is serving the community with rich flavor foods at an excellent price.

Keep in mind this is a food stall in the market. In other words it is not a typical restaurant. There is seating.

But don't let the deter you, the range of flavors were amazing. I wish had more time to explore every dish.

Easy location to get to via the BTS and it's located across from the Imperial World Shopping mall.

location.address: 222 Vibhavadi Rangsit Rd, Sanambin, Don Mueang, Bangkok 10210, Thailand
location.name: Don Mueang International Airport

properties.review_text_published:
Easy to navigate and the immigration progress was super smooth.

Huge thanks to all the staff. I really like the way they cue foreign passport holders. The line seems to move quicker.

location.address: 33, Lorong Madras, 10400 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
location.name: Luk Yea Yan Vegetarian Restaurant

properties.review_text_published:
When it comes to well flavor dishes this is the best restaurants in Penang. I ate at nearby locations and their food is not.as fresh Luk Yes Yan.

The buffet is a must try. You can sample several dishes to get a sense of what you favor the most.

I kind wish I ate all my meal here because other locations didn't even compare in leaving me fully satisfied.

The staff are friendly and hard working. They are dedicated to serving plant-based food to the community. And the prices is great for all wallets.

If you are traveling to Penang make sure to add this shop to your list.

Cheers!

location.address: 100, Jalan Burma, 10050 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
location.name: Tune Hotel George Town Penang

properties.review_text_published:
The best thing about this hotel is it's location. Central to just about everything.

I wish the management would add a coin operated laundry facilities on the ground floor. But there is a small washing machine on the 2nd floor along with irons and ironing boards. And a refrigerator and microwave available. Huge plus.

I could tell this was once a really nice property. But based on my room and overall appearance there are lots of upgrades needed and a few items in the room for convenience would be great.

Here's a list of recommendations for consideration:

Have one dedicated plug for electronics so guests can charge phones, cameras and other devices when the magnetic key card is not in use. One electrical socket with USB terminals.

Add a luggage rack or table under the clothing rack.

A way to dim the lights would be nice.

Other than that the staff was friendly and helpful.

location.address: 24, Jalan Kedah, 10050 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
location.name: Bock Garden Meatless Cafe

properties.review_text_published: I ordered the Wantan Noodle Soup. I can't believe locals are getting this version. I am actually disappointed how bland this dish was. My chef mind was like this could have been so much better with a few simple ingredients. I won't eat here again.

location.address: 48, Jalan Argyll, George Town, 10050 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia
location.name: Laundry Hub Georgetown

properties.review_text_published:
Easy and efficient. This location appears to be active so plan to wait for loads ahead to finish.

The dryer are super hot. Med heat is probably the most you need for a 10 kg load which will cost you 2 tokens (2 MYR).

I was completed satisfied with the washer as well. I did have some residue on one of my collared shirts. I am sure it was from a customer not checking their pockets.

Future customers please double check your pockets so the next person doesn't have to pay the price of having clothes ruined, stained, or spoiled.

And please don't wear your shoes as requested. My feet were dirty simply walking barefoot there. I wasn't please about that.

location.address: 49-51, Jalan Hang Lekiu, City Centre, 50100 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
location.name: Arenaa Star Hotel

questions.question: Rooms
questions.text_answer: Read all the reviews before booking.

questions.question: Can you share more about these topics?

properties.review_text_published:
I've been hoodwinked. The photos make this place look like it's luxury property. Run. It's a trap. I mean it.

Kudo to whoever you hire for your photos they made your property look more than what it is.

The only thing that is luxury is the lobby and the elevator. You.can clearly see there are necessary upgrades required.

If I saw this before making the reservation I would have declined.

Everything goes downhill once you get off the elevator. Dark and dingy. It would make a great setting for a movie location.

Still scratching my head about the use of "luxury" in their description.

One of the fastest systems. Easy to navigate and lots of shops for foods, gifts, clothing, electronics and more.

The bathroom are super clean and appreciate the the water refill stations.

I recently returned to this restaurant after not being there  for several years. I was really excited to enjoy a nice meal. I am not sure what happened with my order. There were only two other customers is the restaurant. I could understand if they had a full house but that was not that case.

I ordered for a large salad and I got a small one. I told the wait staff that I ordered a large salad. She said it was a large salad then return and sorry they made a mistake. I waited for for a correction but nothing.

The owner asked, "How is the meal? I said, "I ordered for a large salad." She apologized and share it was her fault. Then said she didn't think I could finish a large salad. I was so disappointed. I didn't bother ordering anything else at the point. I left discouraged and hungry. I won't be back.

properties.review_text_published:
This location is just inside the medina so it's relatively easy to get to. Very nice settings with the typical home feel.

There are lots of food choices for all diets. And the breads are absolutely incredible.

Please take note that the food is not as full flavored as I expected. Morocco has a rich selection of local spices that can take you to the moon and back.

The dishes we ordered only took us to Gibraltar. I asked the manager what happened, he said because they serve so many Westerners they don't go all in with the spices. Even after I requested to go all in it still was on the light side.

I cannot express how I felt when I heard that. I get his point. But let me decide that for myself. I have to admit I felt slighted after hunting for the slightest hint of spices. A great Tangine will have you licking your fingers in delight.

I would return here for there bread making class. Looks like people were having a great time.

properties.review_text_published:
When you find yourself in Chiang Mai, Thailand it is essential to visit this spiritual and historical Wat (temple).

It's one of the most peaceful sanctuaries in Chiang Mai that will dazzle your eyes.

Take time to embrace the years of dedication generated by the Thai people and the monks.

If you are fortunate to attend during special Buddhist holidays you will be joyfully invited to sit and participate.

You don't have to speak Thai to appreciate the Dharma talks to experience the peace and tranquility.

Many Thais believe that if you pay respect to this temple and a few others your life journey will be prosperous.

Chiang Mai is a rich ancient and modern city that is beloved by Thais and millions of world travelers.

Find yourself there and see what is there for you.

Satwatdee Khrap!

location.address: 2929 S Binion Rd, Apopka, FL 32703, United States
location.name: Magnolia Park Campground

properties.review_text_published:
Impressive campground and park. Big treasure in a small package. This is a great location for RV camping. The price is amazing compared to private campground that pack them in right.

Even though it's a small location, each campsite has ample space between them so you don't feel like you are encroaching on the other campers. Looks like each site comfortably can manage a fifth wheel, Class C and Class B. Not sure about a Class A though.

Each site has electric and water hookups. There are bathrooms with hot showers. And even a sanitation station that is free for registered campers. Otherwise it's $5.

Make sure you plan in advance and be ready to move quickly on registering. This site fills up super quick.

Also, walk across the street and enjoy the sunset from the pier.

I would definitely stay here again!

Note to those that register and are a no show. It would be courteous of you to call and cancel when your plans change. It a shame a site goes unused when there are people ready to occupy it.

Spoke with the staff and shared that happened with two sites with no shows.

properties.review_text_published:
Jai Mahavir! It took me a moment to locate this wonderful Jain Temple on Google maps to write this review.

At the time I visited, I didn't have the address or name in 2016. I was recently reading a Jain book and felt strongly to search online for Jain Temple Hyderabad. It took me only a few seconds to locate it.

I want to thanks everyone for welcoming me to this auspicious Jain Temple. This was my first time visiting a Jain Temple. The energy was not only uplifting but also I felt something that I cannot put into words. The best I can say is pure energy and devotion.

I want to thank the gentleman (I pray that you remember me) that provided me the address to the Jain Temple in Aler. I didn't return as quickly to India as planned to thank you in person. Dear sir, thank you for your generosity and heart.

I would love to reconnect with you and share my experience receiving darshan and the few english books there on Jainism and specifically Preksha Meditation.

I know it must have been very odd for a foreigner from the USA to arrive at your temple doorsteps without an invitation or full insight of Jainism. As I shared, I want to learn more. And you were honest in sharing one of the Jain treasured sites.

Also, a big thank you to the young men that were generous in accepting me in the space and making sure I ate well. (The food was indeed blessed and taste divine.)

I hope someone from the Jain Temple reads this and finds a way to contact me. My humble apologies that it took this long for me to reach you.

Jai Mahavir!

#agentbey

Update: I am marking this review down to one star due to several issues that I discovered over the last year. I recently located the invoice so I am able to update my original review.

1 ‚Äì The steering column no longer locks as it did before. My suspicions is that the technician didn't complete the Safety Recall. See number 2.

2 ‚Äì The gear shift lever issue is back.

3 ‚Äì During a air filter change I found orange peels in the carburetor. This was the last location that I surrendered my vehicle for repair that I was out of my sight. Only someone with ill intention would do something like that.

To all customers that have place their trust in this dealership. Don't! Check your vehicle thoroughly before leaving. Have another technician follow up with the repairs. My biggest regret was going to this dealer because I am not a resident and unable to confront them in person.

The tofu nori was not much to write about. I‚Äôve had this dish at other Chinese vegan restaurants and even in Beijing. This seems like someone might have been inspired with the dish but didn‚Äôt have the technique and flavor range mastered. I wouldn‚Äôt recommend this item.

The bbq seitan was a complete flop. The wheat meat presentation was good but when I saw that the sauce was poured on top and not pan fried in the sauce I knew from a glance it wasn‚Äôt going to the best it could be.

What makes bbq good as a technique is the ‚Äúmeat‚Äù is cooked in the sauce and get caramelized it such a way it coats the ‚Äúmeat‚Äù.

properties.review_text_published:
I've been a fan of Goldie pre-pandemic. The quality has definitely changed with the falafel sandwich.

I've eaten all all locations in the past and was impressed with the universal quality at that time.

The manager was super present at all locations at various times.

What has changed for one the veggies would be cut smaller for one. The cabbage would be well shredded. My sandwich had super size chucks with tough cabbage bits. (That tough part of the cabbage that you generally toss.)

The chunk sizes would go well for a salad but not a sandwich. And what happened to the hummus. It not the same. I feel so deflated now.

Today, it's a 3 star rating for this location. Because I remember when it was 5 stars.

I was impressed with the family vibe and excellent customer service.

The bonus was everyone sharing stories and life experiences. Highly recommend making an appointment.

Thank again Lisa and staff.

location.address: 7121 Ogontz Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19138, United States
location.name: Pennsylvania Department of Transportation - Driver License Center, West Oak Lane

properties.review_text_published:
Second time at this location. Photo ID processed in less than ten minutes of taking the photo.

Very easy steps. Wait for your number to be called. Present your signature card. Then sit in the chair for your photo and thereafter sign your name on the input device.

After a few questions on the screen. Then be seated as your ID is being made. Your name is called and you sign your name to verify you have received your new id.

And that is it.

I went Saturday morning before opening and there was a line of 30 people ahead of me.

location.address: Warren, PA 16365, United States
location.name: Hearts Content Recreation Site

properties.review_text_published:
Very peaceful campgrounds. I could definitely spend more time at this site.

It has the perfect setup! Vault toilets, potable water, campsites, and dumping station.

The planners put in some thought for this site because it also has a playground area and open field for outdoor play.

There are nearby trails throughout the Allegheny National Forest. What a gem!!

location.address: 2543 W Devon Ave, Chicago, IL 60659, United States
location.name: Udupi Palace Restaurant | Best vegetarian Indian Restaurant in Chicago

properties.review_text_published:
I am a huge connoisseur of Indian cuisine. I ordered a staple dish, Masala Dosa. The sambhar lack a range of spicy and the consistency was watery.

The Dosa crepe was average and the potato filling lacked mustard seeds, curry leaves, and ginger which are the base ingredients for the masala of Masala Dosa.

Very disappointed. üôÅ I should have read the reviews from previous customers. I will not be returning.

location.address: 2340 W Grandview Blvd, Erie, PA 16506, United States

properties.review_text_published:
It's rare that I've encountered a five star laundromat. But I have to say from the moment I walked in the door, I knew that this business is cared for with love and attention.

Everything from the bathroom to the machines themselves are super clean. They are even polished. Zero laundromat smells that we have all become accustomed too. It's even air conditioned. Wow!

The prices are really good! Anyone living in the area should be happy to have such an awesome business.

location.address: 4626 3rd Ave, Detroit, MI 48201, United States
location.name: Street Beet

properties.review_text_published:
I am always excited to take a detour to order from a vegan establishment while I am on my road trip.

Bad news my friends the food didn't spark anything for me. First, the fries at the top of the container were fresh about half through the rest of the bunch were twice fried fries that were dry and limp.

Next the "OG Fake Chicken" sandwich. The mayo is probably the best thing about it. I would have been happy to have that mayo and lettuce with tomato than whatever that "OG Fake Chicken" is made of. Actually, I already know. Frozen slab of tofu in an uneventful batter coating. I cannot prove this but based on customer photos of the same sandwich I get the impression the fryer oil needs to be changed.

If I weren't on the road driving I would have gone back to express my distaste in person.

It would be unvegan of me to hate but I can say I disliked this food experience.

properties.review_text_published:
First time customer and lover of vegan Vietnamese food. I am traveling and was very excited to try out the vegan goodness at All Chay.

Started diving into the summer Rolls with the homemade peanut sauce. Completely fresh and super tasty. The fried tofu added a nice chew and taste.

The terrakki noodle salad is super good. Wow! What an amazing array of flavors and textures. The bun (noodles) were also fresh. The only thing the was missing for me was fresh mint leaves. I don't remember if this dish comes with mint or not. Being a lover of Vietnamese food, I did expect it. But the didn't stop the food joy.

Highly recommend. And to the residents of Salt Lake, you have a gem in the neighborhood.

They have some of the best selections of men's watches and the prices are great! Highly recommend for a no hassle purchase.

I want to thank you again for a pleasant an  equitable buying experience.

location.address: I-5, Aurora, OR 97002, United States

Even though it is recommended to go to the furthest parking area, I would say the second parking is a better option.

I am here now at the furthest parking area, while I don't hear the interstate traffic, the occupants here are noisy with the vehicle doors opening and closing, rumbling mufflers on older vans and RVs, and people just roaming about having conversations with invisible tenants.

Be alert and bring earplugs. Also, furthest area reeks of urine.

location.address: I-5, Jefferson, OR 97352, United States

My only complaint is that people discarding trash all over. I really don't understand the logic of that. These beautiful natural settings don't need our waste.

Please take your trash with you!

location.address: 116 Main St, Onalaska, WA 98570, United States

The washer I used was a 3 load washer. More that what I needed. Paid $5.00 which is more than what I normally pay for laundry however given that quality of the wash, I have no complaints.

When you need clean clothes you need clean clothes. The dryer cost .25 cents for 7 minutes which is really good.

The bathroom was also super clean and stocked with hand towels and soap. That is a plus.

I am just traveling through.

location.address: 1601 NW Louisiana Ave, Chehalis, WA 98532, United States

Got me right in and started the tire installation at 7:00 AM.

I got the Dextero All Terrain DAT1 tires for my Class B van. The price is really good.

location.address: Deming, NM 88030, United States

location.name: Evans Creek Campground

properties.review_text_published:
I enjoyed a four day camping trip at Evans Creek Campground. The raw natural setting with the ice cold creek made the experience delightful.

Stayed in my Class B on a nice leveled spot. Each site has a fire pit and picnic table.

Please take your trash with you. I've seen several bottles in the fire pits. Again take ALL trash with you.

These locations are our national treasures. They are only valuable when we treat them with care.

Make certain you have good tires and be alert. Right after the single lane bridge the 7 miles road to the campsite is all gravel. The day I was going to up there were two trucks with flat tires.

And as far as cell expect none. Enjoy nature.

location.address: 410 Gladmar Rd, Thorp, WA 98946, United States
location.name: Shree‚Äôs Travel Plaza

This is the first time after traveling for 6-months around the US using this debit card and not have it be counted as cash.

The clerk affirmed "cash" is actual cash and not a debit card.

properties.review_text_published:
Shopped for a few items for the RV. Spoke with staff and only one night is allowed for overnight stay.

Please remember your are a guest. Please don't leave garage and waste for someone else to manage.

There are a few trash bins near the front of the store.

The train behind the store runs pretty much all night. The horn is sounded somewhere between 1 PM and 7:30 AM.

Be mindful of your surroundings and valuables. I did noticed several individuals strolling about in the parking lot.

location.address: 78 WA-115, Ocean Shores, WA 98569, United States
location.name: Quinault Beach Resort and Casino

properties.review_text_published:
Very easy process to check in with an RV. After completing the check in with security, you will be directed to go to the reception station to register.

There you'll be given a form to complete. You'll need to provide your ID and choice of payment. Once your transaction is complete you be given a hang tag to place in your vehicle.

Process took no longer than 5 minutes.

Then drive over to the designated area for RVs and pick a spot and enjoy your stay.

location.address: Waddell Creek Rd SW, Olympia, WA 98512, United States
location.name: Middle Waddell Campground

properties.review_text_published:
Very conveniently located just outside of Tumwater, Olympia. Just a 20 minutes drive for me.

Take note this site requires that you have the Discover Pass to stay. The length of stay is 7-days.

I purchased the annual pass from Walmart for a total of $35. Well, worth the price.

There are no trash receptacles. Please be responsible and manage your waste.

There are vault toilets available. No RV dump station. Plan according to dump at a rest area.

This is a motorized vehicle site so expect to hear ATVs, quads, and dirt bikes. Also, there will be sprinkle of gun fire in the background. At the time of my stay the gun fire was heard in the late morning to early afternoon.

At dusk things were quiet during my stay.

I spoke with the host on several occasions and they a passionate about being camp hosts. Very informative conversations and provided some nice details of other campgrounds.

I would visit again in the future.

location.address: 4804 Pacific Ave SE, Lacey, WA 98503, United States
location.name: kamakura japanese cuisine

properties.review_text_published:
This has to be the best vegan sushi in the United States that hands down have thoroughly dazzled my taste buds.

The individual care for flavors, textures, and visual presentation were A1. This impressive Vegan Sampler platter is off menu but I highly recommend ordering this food journey. It is completely worth it. You will not be disappointed.

Kamakura team your delivery of vegan sushi sets a standard in the culinary world.

It is obviously you took time to pioneer and expand vegan options for everyone.

Arigatou from Chef Bey.

location.address: 2823 S Oak St, Port Angeles, WA 98362, United States
location.name: Heart O' the Hills Campground

properties.review_text_published:
Excellent campsite location. The payment system is much better than using cash like most campsites.

Bathrooms are clean. I first stayed in Loop A. The sites aren't level so I recommend having leveling blocks. There is drinking water as well as dumpster.

I decided to extend my stay for two more days in Loop C. I prefer Loop C over Loop A.

There is a trail head located at Loop E - Heart of the Forest. Highly recommend trekking this trail. It was muddy in some areas. But worth every step of the way.

50% off of $24 with the America the Beautiful Annual Pass.

location.address: 1190 Thomas St, Seattle, WA 98109, United States
location.name: Kati Vegan Thai

properties.review_text_published:
I was very excited to have some high rated Thai food today. Especially, vegan Thai. It's rare to find in the US.

Being a Vegan Chef, I was expecting to have my taste buds dazzled with the blends of carmel like flavor of palm sugar evenly blended with soy sauce and tamarind nicely combined with the Pad Thai flat rice noodles.

The levels of disappointed were immense. All I could taste is tamarind paste. The menu says Old Style Pad Thai. Whatever rendition this was was not true to Thai cuisine.

I speak from experience living in Thailand and as a chef that explore many of the traditional flavors of Thailand.

For $14.00 it was awful. To the head chef / manager, please reevaluate that recipe.

Khap khun khrap.

location.address: 7239 Martin Way E, Lacey, WA 98516, United States
location.name: Lacey Laundry

properties.review_text_published:
Fresh and so clean. I've been to several throughout the US. And this is one of the best I've experienced so far. The attendants keep the place super clean. The machine look new!

As a traveler this is very important. Because sometimes I may drive to a laundromat and it's smells bad and dirty.

The prices are very good too. You can pay with card or use quarters. Very convenient all around.

The bathrooms were clean as well.

It has a family vibe and feels like is operated by people that actual care. That makes a world of a difference.

The dryers are 25 cents for 4 minutes. In my experience the dryer high temperature took awhile to heat up. Machines 21 and 23.

Please continue being awesome. Muchas Gracias!
