I got the large bento box. Wow! They stuffed it with a lot of wonderful treats.

Very filling! I love being plant based. I get to eat good everyday.

These restaurant was recommended and I am very happy to have had a chance to experience the food. The prices are really good too.

location.address: 9324 Garvey Ave, South El Monte, CA 91733, United States
location.name: Veggie Life Restaurant

properties.review_text_published:
Amazing and delicious food delivered by a hard working team. The arrays of flavors will take you to Vietnam for sure.

I completely enjoyed all the dishes. The portions are excellent for the price.

First had the mock beef noodle, bun bo hue, and that was supper good. The right amount of spice and lots of fresh items such as bean sprouts and mint basil.

I later ordered another dish that I used to get in Vietnam. I comes with noodles, spring rolls, vegan beef, vegan fish sauce, pickled carrots and jimaca root, and a mocked shredded pork. It has a nice combo of sweet, sour, and a little spice.

Wow! Sooooooo good. I could eat here everyday and not have the same thing twice.

Exceptional massage. I was frustrated going to different massage businesses trying to find one that actually focused on technique.

Toda, I was blessed to have a 90 minute massage today's that reigned supreme. Mora really focused on relaxing the stress in my neck.

I feel so much better. I will return for another treatment. Absolutely, amazing. I feel sooooooo much better.

location.name: Tempe Auto Repair

properties.review_text_published:
Highly recommend the team at Tempe Auto Repair and especially Gilbert for investigating the mystery sound coming from my Class B Van.

I first spoke with Jake in the early AM. He said, "Come back around noon. We will get you in and see what the issue is."

I returned and within minutes they were ruling out possible problems.

Within 30 minutes they came to a conclusion that the issue is with the leaf springs.

From start to finish they were thorough and got me back on the road. I appreciate people that love their craft.

Definitely, going back in the near future.

#excellence #trustworthy

properties.review_text_published:
I ordered the fresh rolls. They were very tasty and the peanut sauce was flavorful. The order comes with three rolls.

Overall, I enjoyed the interaction and service.

However, I have a concern because I specifically requested no onion or garlic in my red curry dish. I was told they can make without.

But I discover later that there was garlic in the curry. I had an allergic reaction. Obviously, I didn't die. But when you are in food service you really have to be mindful of food allergens.

The fact is that it would have taken only  10 seconds to read the label. I could have easily ordered another dish.

I called the next day to inquire about the ingredients of the curry paste and the woman said, "yes, it's has garlic."

I strongly advise management and staff to be more informed of products ingredients they are using.

More on garlic allergy:
https://www.healthline.com/health/garlic-allergy

I was super happy to learn that there's a Thai Vegan restaurant in Phoenix. I just arrived and got myself over to this shop immediately. I had a great server and soon as I heard him speak I was transported back to my time in Thailand.

As a vegan chef I am big on authenticity and flavors. The vegan Thai Ice Tea was just right. The flavor was as I expected and remembered from living in Thailand.

The fresh summer rolls we're almost a full meal. Very robust in flavor and then sauce was absolutely yummy.

I ordered the Pad Thai which was good but a bit different than what I know Pad Thai to be. The rice noodles appeared to have been cooked in water first which made them wet and brittle.

The consistency of the noodle should be more gummy which holds most of the flavor since it get cook in a combo of soy sauce, tamarind, and palm sugar in it's dry state. Typically, Pad Thai is served with a slice of lime and toasted peanuts.

I did ask for lime but got lemon. Not the same but what can you do.

I would definitely eat here again and mostly likely will. I am curious to try the other dishes.

properties.review_text_published:
I am completely impressed with the Sam's Club at this location.

I've been to probably over 30 Sam's Club locations in the US.

This is a five star raving review of this Sam's Club location.

First of all the design of the exterior of the building looks really good. It's modern. It's fresh. It's inviting.

In other words, everything is working and it's well lit.

Even the gas station looks updated and much more fresher looking than any other one I've ever been to.

But Sam's Club would not be Sam's Club without the people, the actual employees, and the management.

As I walked around the store I saw the different employees and they look genuinely happy like they wanted to be there and it created a friendly atmosphere.

And I got a sense that there is a strong presence of teamwork throughout the whole establishment.

This is probably the first time I ever wrote a review this long for Sam's Club.

Kudos to the manager of this location because it takes a good manager to lead a good team and to create such an atmosphere that's to me that is very vibrant and just genuinely open.

I actually wished I lived in this city so I could go to this Sam's Club. Lol.

I just want to say thank you to all the Sam's Club team and the management for all you do.

location.address: 8016 Tara Blvd, Jonesboro, GA 30236, United States
location.name: Valvoline Instant Oil Change

properties.review_text_published:
UPDATE: While the customer service was great. However, I am livid that some fluid was leaking just days after. My camper van isn't a daily ride vehicle. It's basically parked for 5-6 days out of the week. And I didn't have a leak prior to the oil change service.

I was keeping track of this leak and tried to visit several mechanics to confirm what the issue might be. I did take the van back to this location and the attendant confirmed it was transmission fluid leaking.

Finally, located a mechanic with a lift that could inspect the issue. The rubber hoses on the Transmission Cooler Unit were blown out most likely to the transmission fluid being overfilled.

It cost me $488 for the repair! I am not a happy camper. This is an unexpected expense that really hurts my wallet. That doesn't include the oil service of $58.31.

I don't have a trend of leaving poor rating for businesses but I am feeling the pain of someone inability to pay attention.

ORIGINAL REVIEW:
The best in customer service. Love their pitstop style service. Makes huge difference.

location.address: 2968 N Decatur Rd, Decatur, GA 30033, United States
location.name: AAMCO Transmissions & Total Car Care

properties.review_text_published:
I will only state facts and no opinions. I came in to have a transmission leaking issue diagnosed.

The service technicians informed me that the transmission lines needed to be replaced along with the transmission cooling unit. And the cost would be $900 total. An OEM transmission cooling unit would have to be ordered from a dealer and that would take up to a week.

I said I would take a few days to consider. And as recommended make sure to check the transmission fluid.

Today, I checked the lines from the transmission pan to the radiator. And there are zero breaks or leaks.

I looked at the transmission cooling unit and it is dry as dirt. No leaks as I was informed.

I focused back to the area where the fluid appears on the ground. And to my surprise the intake line just needs to be tightened. How the technicians missed that is beyond me.

location.name: Zostel Agra

properties.review_text_published:
The best thing going for this location is it's location. 1 KM from the East Gate entrance. Walking distance from the Taj Ticket Counter. There are some local shops nearby for local eats and beverages.

I'll keep this review plain and clear:
‚Ä¢ Needs to be thoroughly cleaned each day. The bathroom aren't cleaned each day.
‚Ä¢ AC didn't work for the days reserved. Problem related to electrical issues.
‚Ä¢ Hot water barely got warm. Problem related to electrical issues.
‚Ä¢ Very attentive staff.
‚Ä¢ One night music when on until 11:30 PM. Not sure if this is a Friday night thing.
‚Ä¢ Food I don't know. After looking at the kitchen I declined.

Personal recommendation is if you plan to stay there make it one night tops. I really wish the place was cleaner. The wifi internet speed is very good. This is a huge plus for travelers. Especially, in India. Many places promised fast but fall short. Zostel gets two thumbs up for fast internet.

location.address: B 36/4-12 Sankat Mochan Road Near Sankat Mochan Mandir Saket Nagar, Rampuri Colony, Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh 221005, India
location.name: Hotel Raameshvaram Vatika

properties.review_text_published:
The location is excellent even though some of the locals thought is was a bit far from the Ghats. I think as a tourist you need to have some distance between the tourist areas and where you rest.

I went out to look at several hotels near the Ghat and I thought that many of them were substandard. And other great hotel but location was not good. The closer you go into the Ghats it get congested and extremely filthy.

So having found the location by chance was a gift to my time there. When I came back to my room I felt peaceful to be away from all the hagglers, smells, dust, dirt and feces.

The staff is very accommodating. I felt well taking care of during my stay. The management made sure in several instances I was happy with my time there. Happy to provide details of where to go and best options.

There is a very sacred Hanuman Temple - Sankat Mochan Temple just in walking distance. You can actually walk to Assi Ghat from this hotel. Along the way you will find local vendors and some really good fruit blends, chai, fruits, juices, etc. All of which I enjoyed several times a day.

The room size is very nice and bathroom is western style. The room is clean. If you aren't use to the heat I would recommend getting an A/C room. The bed is very huge king size bed. Three people could actually sleep on the bed.

I came in late from the airport and the staff took care to make sure I had a room. The provided quick service in making sure I got to my room. I got the cold bottle of water I ordered within a few minutes.

I would recommend to travelers to serious consider this hotel despite the distance. Peace of mind is more valuable than a location. And as others have share this is the cleanest area of the city.

Impressive room. Excellent size and modern design. I was complete satisfied with the room and the location isn't the best. Seems like an industrial area that is being transformed. The biggest feature of delights with the bathtub. Traveling in Asia and discovering a bathtub is such a treat.

There was one small problem the bathtub stopper didn't work. That was remedied by stuffing a small towel into the drain. The breakfast is average but there is no official seating and tables yet. This is a new hotel. It appears there is something there for everyone to eat. The one issue I had with the management not informing me that the room aren't cleaned unless you ask them. It was stated this is policy and directed me to a post on the other side of the counter.

I asked them to please inform guests when they check in. They were nice to bring up sheet and towels. And provide another bottle of water. During check out the managing staff member eagerly asked me how was my stay and if there was any recommendations. I share the same sentiment about the cleaning room policy. He took offense to my simple suggestion and wanted to challenge me with a set of reasons. I politely asked him to consider.

The WIFI in this establishment is super slow. If you need continuous access and speed then you may want to book another hotel. I hope the manager will take on the practice of notifying guest of the cleaning room policy.

location.address: 8JGH+47M, 6th Main Rd, Vani Vilas Mohalla, Mysuru, Karnataka 570002, India
location.name: Udupikar's Veg Restaurant

properties.review_text_published:
Great Portions, Excellent Flavor and Awesome Service

This is one of the best restaurants I've encountered during my travels in India. The staff is attentive in making certain your dietary needs are met. Not a rice grain was left after I devoured my meal.

Clean setting with a visual tribute to USA musicians and vocalists. This restaurant is frequented by locals and travelers alike.

A nice variety of menu selections and the vegetarian meals are freshly prepared. Meals can be prepared without onion and garlic. The cooks are masterful at keeping the flavors rich and scrumptious to the very end.

Don't miss this quiet and cozy restaurant when you are in Mysore.

location.address: 573/7, Jangali Maharaj Rd, next to Sambhaji Park, Shivajinagar, Pune, Maharashtra 411004, India
location.name: Hotel Sapna

properties.review_text_published:
This property is indeed a two-star moth ball / moldy hotel. The room is dark. Based on what a few guest wrote it is pretty accurate. Dingy is the word. Overpriced for what you get. The only redeeming quality is some of staff is friendly and breakfast selections were good. This property has so much potential to be a great hotel with some upgrades and some deep cleaning. Why does 2 stars have to be dirty?

I have no intention of ever staying there again. Much better hotels in the area for the same price and quality customer service.

properties.review_text_published:
Sulonda provide a very direct and caring counseling service. She was committed to helping me discover the blocks that were hindering me in having fruitful relationship.

I highly recommend Sulonda for anyone who is ready for a dynamic transformation in their life.

Thank you Sulonda for your insight and wisdom.

The staff was very friendly, however, my room was not. Upon arriving in my room I quickly notice black mold on the ceiling in the bathroom and sleep area right over the bed. I immediately requested for another room. Got a different room. Took off my shoes and noticed the floss felt grimy so I took a tissue and wiped it on the floor and it turn to a dark earth color. They say premium bedding. That is not the true. It is old and spotted with stains. The pillows were old and stain with spots as well. There was hair on the bed as well. Even the walls were dirty. In my state of dissatisfaction I was challenged with do I stay or do I go.

My expectations were based on the reviews and on every count this hotel failed to deliver. So I chose to fly out like a bat in the night. Thanks to my Reward Silver, this reservation was cancelled. In a matter of minutes I was being met the van of the new hotel and transported just minutes away.
